,Not Recommended,229890,28455477,"Posted: 18 December, 2016",all,Renegade Master,"I cannot recommend Joe Danger to the average gamer, as I can only recommend it to experts at bike games due its huge downsides:-Collecting is required for level/stage advancement, not just obtaining scores for trophies.  It'd be one thing if a ""star"" required to unlock levels were like ""collect 40 of 50 specific things"", but its more like ""collect all 50 things"" which turns this game into a tedious challenge once you reach certain stages that require stars. This stopped the game dead in its tracks for me after getting through a few percent of career and training modes.-""Full controller support"" is a lie. Lane changes either cannot be performed with a controller, or they're restricted to limited areas.  Also, multiple controllers for split screen are not supported!-Only Xbox controller controls are shown & explained in game.  Keyboard controls can only be seen and configured using the pregame launcher app.The upsides to this game might be enough for bike game experts:-Level building & steam workshop is pretty extensive.-Absurd number of unlocks and in-level collectables.-Leaderboards, ghosts, and split screen."
