,Recommended,229890,7782220,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,Faseeh,"Joe Danger. Go in expecting nothing. And this will blow your mind.There's a little charm about Joe Danger. It's like your Excitebike in 3D with your mission based gameplay and speed and exploration in a linear progression based game. It's hilarious. It reeks off 70s to 90s and if you're from that time or you like those times, you'll love this.Joe Danger is about a retired stuntsman who wants to rejoin and get back his skills and audience. You take on the role of that guy and you bring him on the road to success. Not much of a story but this game's all about the gameplay.With tons of replayability, nooks and carrines to explore, a whole lot of missions, this game is well worth its price!"
